    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1959-03-11T19:26:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1959-03-11T19:26:00-05:00" n="101"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                <head>101. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d101fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 700.5/3–1159. Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MBRH1"
                            >McBride</persName>; cleared by <persName corresp="#p_TBELIII1"
                            >Timmons</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_GJNJ1">Greene</persName>, and
                            <persName corresp="#p_MRD1">Murphy</persName>; and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1959-03-11T19:26:00">March 11, 1959, 7:26
                            p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3320. Embassy pass <gloss target="#t_USRO1">USRO</gloss> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_TRL1">Thurston</persName>. Department has noted curious
                    discrepancy between <persName corresp="#p_DEGC1">deGaulle</persName>’s attitude
                    on tripartite talks taken with Secretary in February in Paris<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d101fn1">See <ref target="#d95">Document 95</ref>.</note> and that
                    expressed to <persName corresp="#p_SPH1">Spaak</persName> recently both by
                        <persName corresp="#p_DEGC1">deGaulle</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_DEL1">deLeusse</persName>.<note n="2" xml:id="d101fn2">See <ref
                            target="frus1958-60v07p1#d198">Part 1, Documents 198</ref> and <ref
                            target="frus1958-60v07p1#d199">199</ref>.</note> Embassy will recall
                    that in February <persName corresp="#p_DEGC1">deGaulle</persName> expressed
                    relative satisfaction with progress which talks had made. It is therefore
                    disturbing note this now adduced by <persName corresp="#p_DEGC1"
                        >deGaulle</persName> as a reason for his most unfortunate action re French
                    fleet.</p>
                <p>As you know we attach considerable significance to these tripartite talks. We
                    have certainly made no decision break them off, though we have paused to review
                    situation and are not now planning renew these talks until after <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> meeting.<note n="3" xml:id="d101fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_AH1">Alphand</persName> met with <persName
                            corresp="#p_MRD1">Murphy</persName> on March 11; see <ref
                            target="frus1958-60v07p1#d201">Part 1, Document 201</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Herter</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
